    "title": ".",
    "body": "<!-- This issue tracker is only for technical issues related to Bitcoin Core.\r\n\r\nI have a bitcoin Node set up and it has synced to the lastet block but when ever i do the node-upgrade it synchronizes the blockheaders again from start. Is there any way we can avoid as i already have the block downloaded.Please find the logs and docker-compose file.\r\n\r\nLogs :\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:22Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 229998 (~34.96%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:23Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 231998 (~35.25%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:23Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 233998 (~35.54%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:24Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 235998 (~35.83%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:25Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 237998 (~36.13%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:26Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 239998 (~36.41%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:27Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 241998 (~36.69%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:27Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 243998 (~36.98%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:28Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 245998 (~37.26%)\r\n2021-05-26T07:17:28Z Synchronizing blockheaders, height: 247998 (~37.55%)\r\n\r\ndocker-compose.yaml:\r\n\r\nversion: '2'\r\nservices:\r\n    node:\r\n        image: kylemanna/bitcoind:latest\r\n        container_name: bitcoind_container\r\n        restart: always\r\n        ports:\r\n            - \"8333:8333\"\r\n            - \"8334:8332\"\r\n        environment:\r\n            PRINTTOCONSOLE: 1\r\n            RPCUSER: \"xxx\"\r\n            RPCPASSWORD: \"xxx\"\r\n        volumes:\r\n            - $PWD:/bitcoin\r\n        command:\r\n            - \"-onlynet=ipv4\"\r\n            - \"-txindex\"\r\n            - \"-rpcthreads=128\"\r\n            - \"-dbcache=1024\"\r\n            - \"-rpcallowip=0.0.0.0/0\"\r\n            - \"-rpcbind=127.0.0.1\"\r\n            - \"-rpcbind=bitcoind_container\"\r\n            - \"-blocksonly=1\"\r\n        mem_limit: 4g\r\n",
